an><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Regular assessment (suggest by annual review) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of available finance required for supporting non commercially viable services, growth and decline of communities and vehicle availability.  This list is not exhaustive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Dialogue and negotiation with transport providers, local community organisations, emplo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">yers, schools and local health services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people, young people) taken into account in determining the provision of public transport to isolated communities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The specific needs of different groups of disabled passengers are now recognised in law.  Bus and train accessibility is increasingly becoming a reality.  Isolated communities are often served by narrow lanes and together with passenger numbers more sui</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">table sized vehicles may be required.  For example a 15 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">seater</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> bus compliant with the latest DDA regulations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-17.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">What are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities?  How can thes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">e challenges be overcome?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Some of the challenges confronting the provision of public transport in these areas are:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Finance – the availability of support funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Location – narrow roads may require special type of vehicle</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Number of passengers – the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">smaller the number of passengers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the higher the cost of providing a service and this particularly applies to buses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Availability of smaller local transport firms willing to accept this type of contract</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Travel patterns of a limited number of passengers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Trains also need to stop at all stations to provide transport</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> to work and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">back. A lot do this in one direction but not to work places in the opposite direction. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Example.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Ivybridge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> to Plymouth 7.26 arriving 7.40, 7.58 arriving 8.11 in the opposite directi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Ivybridge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> to Exeter first train 8.25 arriving 9.18, not nearly early enough</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These challenges may be overcome through</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The regular assessment to provide match funding, where commercially services are not viable, together with the need to explore all possi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ble funding streams</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Innovative solutions which could include many forms of community transport, taxis and the possibility of the general public using specified school buses where there is space.  The relaxation of start times on senior and disabled bus pa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ss regulations may also be needed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Recognising the differing needs of passengers in isolated areas and rationalising these wherever feasible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Through dialogue and negotiation with organisations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eg</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the local NHS, employer organisations, education department</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s, bus, train, community transport groups and taxi companies to seek and determine possible solutions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Whenever there is an opportunity to promote the use of public transport over the car - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">exploit it.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">How effectively do Community Transport services </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">address the needs of passengers in isolated communities?  How could Community Transport be improved</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Community transport is of ever increasing importance to isolated communities as it is often used to fill gaps in the public transport network.  It can tak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e many forms with funding ranging from local volunteer fund raising to financial support from local transport authorities.  Community transport is effective by using:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Vehicles which are suited to the route(s) needed and the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> groups of passengers using the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">services and may be also be more affordable where local fund raising provides the vehicle</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There can be a greater degree of flexibility for services arranged at local level</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Consideration should be given to raising the age o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">f volunteer drivers from 70 to 75, subject to health and driver ability tests.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Taxis and other demand responsive services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are expensive to use by those living in isolated communities.  Often these people are those whose circumstances have changed with the passage of time and they are no longer able to drive or have the use of a car.  All groups of passengers in these circums</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tances can have widely diverse needs which make resolving the challenges more demanding.  Many living in isolated communities do so in the knowledge that public transport is likely to be limited.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Car schemes (often used for medical appointments) and innova</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tive use of taxis are two approaches which can contribute to the easing of travel costs.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Older people may find the need to move to urban areas to ease the cost of travel.  Young people of working age may also need to more away from rural areas for similar </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reasons.  This has a social impact on the sustainability of villages and hamlets in remote areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities?  How can these services be made more affordable?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The main ch</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">allenges are:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Increasingly limited availability of supporting public funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Low passenger numbers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Possible requirement for specialist vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These services could be made more affordable by:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Flexible thinking by local transport authorities where </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cceptable to “think outside the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">box”</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-indent:-33.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Innovation and a willingness to experiment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-indent:-33.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Find partners, consult and negotiate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-indent:-33.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Seek best practice and share successful solutions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-indent:-33.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Publicise passenger numbers (not percentages) to highlight cost effective </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">visibility</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Subject to finance availability, improve the travel experience quality for users of public transport by extending to use of “Real Time Information” for buses and “Customer Information System” for rail.  These measures together with the wider av</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ailability of shelters, seating and time tables at all stops, may also go some way to persuading car users to change their travel habits</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">   Local knowledge, together with research amongst Senior Voice Devon members and local Councillors and O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fficers, has enabled us to answer the questions often in a positive light.  We are fortunate in having a County Council where both Councillors and Officers take a detailed interest in all forms of public transport.  We have noted they are willing to “look </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outside the box” and to experiment.  They work closely with bus companies, both large and small, and have taken the lead in encouraging and being directly involved in all the Devon rail branch lines becoming </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">members of the Community Rail Partnership.  Whil</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">st there will always be room for improvement and some necessary adjustment of bus routes and timetabling, we note that since April 2012 only one bus service in Devon has been withdrawn entirely.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>